org.diylc.common
Interface IPlugInPort

All Superinterfaces:
IKeyProcessor, IMouseProcessor, ISelectionProcessor, ITemplateProcessor
All Known Implementing Classes:
Presenter
public interface IPlugInPort
extends ISelectionProcessor, IMouseProcessor, IKeyProcessor, ITemplateProcessor

Interface for communication between plug-ins and the application. Plug-ins may acquire information or make changes through this interface. Application events are dispatched to plug-ins through MessageDispatcher

Author:
Branislav Stojkovic
See Also:
IPlugIn, MessageDispatcher, IMessageListener, EventType

getCanvasDimensions

java.awt.Dimension getCanvasDimensions(boolean useZoom)
Returns size of the canvas that takes project dimensions into account as well as zoom level. Each dimension is calculated as the product of the actual size and the number of pixels per unit. If useZoom is set to true, the result is scaled by zoom factor.
